            },
            "id": "c8a3f1e2-1111-0000-0000-000000000016"
          },
          {
            "type": "faq",
            "value": {
              "items": [
                {
                  "question": "What is a Flex Page?",
                  "id": "what-is-a-flex-page",
                  "answer": "<p data-block-key=\"a1\">A Flex Page is a page built from reusable content blocks. You arrange blocks like sections, heroes, and cards to lay out a page without writing any code.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "question": "Do I need a developer to build one?",
                  "id": "need-a-developer",
                  "answer": "<p data-block-key=\"a2\">Nope. Flex Pages use a visual editor, so you can add, reorder, and configure blocks yourself, and new pages publish without any special code.</p>"
                },
                {
                  "question": "How do I add a block to a page?",
                  "id": "how-to-add-a-block",
                  "answer": "<p data-block-key=\"a3\">Open the editor, pick a block, and drop it where you want it. Each block has its own options you can tweak.</p><ul><li data-block-key=\"a3a\">Pick a block</li><li data-block-key=\"a3b\">Drop it on the page</li><li data-block-key=\"a3c\">Configure its options</li></ul>"
                }
              ],
              "config": []
            },
            "id": "c8a3f1e2-2222-0000-0000-000000000001"
          },
          {
            "type": "section",
            "value": {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "<h3 data-block-key=\"faqe2\">Multiple answers open, custom accent color, H2 headings</h3>",
                  "id": "c8a3f1e2-1111-0000-0000-000000000017"
                }
              ],
              "config": [
                {
                  "type": "padding",
                  "value": 1,
